SUMMARY:Engineers in the C-Suite: Leslie Duke\, Chair and CEO of Burns & Mc
	Donnell
DTSTAMP:20260622T021944Z
DTSTART:20261022T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:ABOUT THE SPEAKERA proven leader in the workplace and industry\
	, Leslie Duke paved the way for countless employee-owners\, community memb
	ers and students through her mentorship and leadership.  A registered Prof
	essional Engineer with a B.S. in Civil Engineering\, Leslie has spent her 
	career strengthening and supporting the communities in her home state of T
	exas and across the U.S. &#160\;She became Burns &amp\; McDonnell's eighth
	 CEO in 2024.  An entrepreneur at heart\, Leslie joined the company in the
	 late 1990s as an engineer in the Houston office's transmission and distri
	bution services group\, inspired by the employee ownership model. &#160\;S
	ince then\, she has held numerous leadership positions and has helped esta
	blish six offices.  She helped expand the firm's customer base from one lo
	cal Houston client to more than 650 local\, regional and national clients 
	in the industrial\, refining\, chemical\, manufacturing and power utility 
	markets. &#160\;During her tenure\, the business delivered over $5 billion
	 in engineering\, procurement\, construction\, environmental and consultin
	g services from the region.  &#160\;  __  &#160\;ABOUT THE ENGINEERS IN TH
	E C-SUITE SPEAKER SERIES  Hosted by the Rice Center for Engineering Leader
	ship (RCEL) (https://www.rcelconnect.org/)\, Engineers in the C-Suite feat
	ures executives and thought leaders from technology organizations who uniq
	uely employ or depend on engineers. &#160\;These accomplished leaders shar
	e experiences in navigating change and how engineers can equip themselves 
	to lead the way. &#160\;Through this series\, learn about how products and
	 workplaces are being disruptively transformed through technological advan
	cements\, and how engineers are expected to not just adapt to but lead thi
	s transformation.  Previous Engineers in the C-Suite speakers include:Mark
	 Lashier\, Chairman and CEO\, Phillips 66 (Fall 2025)    (video: https://w
	ww.youtube.com/watch?v=9Oql-Yp92lg&amp\;t=19s (https://www.youtube.com/wat
	ch?v=9Oql-Yp92lg&amp\;t=19s))  Sandra Johnson\, CEO of SKJ Visioneering an
	d former CTO of IBM Africa (Fall 2024)    (video: https://www.youtube.com/
	watch?v=wJlT3xvHhIk) (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wJlT3xvHhIk))Antonio
	 Neri\, CEO of Hewlett Packard Enterprise (Spring 2024)    (video: https:/
	/www.youtube.com/watch?v=yBwYQvrfM14&amp\;t=4s) (https://www.youtube.com/w
	atch?v=yBwYQvrfM14&amp\;t=4s))Jim Whitehurst\, former CEO of Red Hat and P
	resident of IBM (Fall 2023)    (video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ty2
	M4Dw9pcg) (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ty2M4Dw9pcg))  &#160\;REGISTRAT
	ION  Check back soon for RSVP link!\n\nhttps://events.rice.edu/live/events
	/429513-engineers-in-the-c-suite-leslie-duke-chair-and-ceo\n\nFrom Rice Un
	iversity - Open to the Public
URL:https://events.rice.edu/live/events/429513-engineers-in-the-c-suite-les
	lie-duke-chair-and-ceo
GEO:29.7174;-95.4018
LOCATION:Duncan Hall
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:rice-public-events
CATEGORIES:Rice University - Open to the Public
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
